# Dotfiles Repo

- Always commit directly to `main` — no feature branches, no PRs
- Use simple descriptive commit style (no conventional commit prefixes)

# Coding

- Make the minimal change needed — don't over-engineer or refactor beyond the ask
- Follow existing code conventions, patterns, and libraries before introducing new ones
- Don't create files, docs, or configs unless explicitly asked
- Never commit secrets, keys, or credentials

# Git Safety

- Never force-push, amend commits, or use `git add -A` without asking
- Never skip hooks (--no-verify) unless asked

# Working Style

- Gather context before concluding root cause — don't jump to fixes
